  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Supporting the Elimination of Modern Slavery Related to the Pacific Fisheries Sector</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">In general, there is a lack of effective policies to guide the monitoring and reporting of potential modern slavery which subsequently limits protection efforts. This also undermines the capacity of companies in countries such as Australia to eradicate modern slavery from their supply chains. This is particularly relevant with the Modern Slavery Bill 2018, which was passed in the Australia House of Representatives and Senate in November 2018. &#xA0;The objective of this project is to contribute to the elimination of modern slavery in the Pacific fishing industry.</narrative>
  </description>
